Java Configuration without using XML (using Annotations equivalents)
1. Configuration done completely in Java code without XML file
2. Replace XML file with Java config class with @COnfiguration annotation
3. @bean annotation same as <bean> tag in XML file
4. Instead of using ClassPathXmlApplicationContext to grab XML config file,
   you will instead use AnnotationConfigApplicationContext
5. The first, or if only one config file, can be added as configName.class as a 
   parameter in the AnnotationConfigApplicationContext. If there are multiple 
   config files, then the config files can then be added using context.register()
